1254
01:34:27,187 --> 01:34:29,855
[FLUTTERING]

1255
01:34:59,010 --> 01:35:00,469
HEATHER:
"The more she read...

1256
01:35:00,637 --> 01:35:03,180
...the more she realized
what she had in her hands...

1257
01:35:03,348 --> 01:35:07,726
...was nothing more or less
than her life itself.

1258
01:35:08,311 --> 01:35:10,562
That everything
she had experienced and thought...

1259
01:35:10,730 --> 01:35:12,815
...was bound within these pages."

1260
01:35:12,983 --> 01:35:14,817
[CLANGS]

1261
01:35:15,860 --> 01:35:18,279
"There was no movie.

1262
01:35:18,446 --> 01:35:20,155
There was only...

1263
01:35:20,323 --> 01:35:21,365
...her life."

1264
01:35:21,533 --> 01:35:23,033
Aah!

1265
01:35:23,201 --> 01:35:24,785
-It's just me.
-Dylan!

1266
01:35:29,833 --> 01:35:31,959
-Are you okay? Are you all right?
-Yeah.

1267
01:35:32,127 --> 01:35:35,129
-Okay. Where's the man?
-I don't know.

1268
01:35:35,297 --> 01:35:37,798
He had me, but then he let me go.

1269
01:35:40,468 --> 01:35:41,635
[HEATHER SCREAMS]

1270
01:35:41,803 --> 01:35:42,845
Meet your maker.

1271
01:35:46,516 --> 01:35:47,725
[SCREAMS]

1272
01:35:54,107 --> 01:35:56,025
Pick a pet for the rug rat, bitch.

1273
01:36:00,655 --> 01:36:02,323
[GRUNTS]

1274
01:36:03,575 --> 01:36:05,743
[GROANING]

1275
01:36:08,163 --> 01:36:09,204
Fuck you!

1276
01:36:09,372 --> 01:36:11,457
[GRUNTS]

1277
01:36:12,250 --> 01:36:14,668
-Mommy!
-Get out of here, Dylan!

1278
01:36:17,380 --> 01:36:19,631
[BOTH GRUNTING]

1279
01:36:36,524 --> 01:36:37,608
DYLAN:
Take this!

1280
01:36:37,776 --> 01:36:39,443
[FREDDY YELLING]

1281
01:36:50,205 --> 01:36:52,998
Come here, my pretty.
I've got some gingerbread for you!

1282
01:36:53,333 --> 01:36:55,834
No! Dylan, run!

1283
01:37:08,264 --> 01:37:09,556
[COUGHING]

1284
01:37:11,643 --> 01:37:13,477
Mommy!

1285
01:37:13,645 --> 01:37:15,896
FREDDY:
Gotcha! Ha!

1286
01:37:21,277 --> 01:37:22,611
Mommy?

1287
01:37:23,405 --> 01:37:26,990
-Mommy!
FREDDY: Mommy!

1288
01:37:27,742 --> 01:37:32,162
Now, where's your mommy,
piglet, huh? Huh?

1289
01:37:32,997 --> 01:37:36,959
[CHANTlNG]
One, two, Freddy's coming for you

1290
01:38:08,575 --> 01:38:10,576
[GRUNTING]

1291
01:38:32,307 --> 01:38:33,474
Dylan?

1292
01:38:33,641 --> 01:38:35,267
DYLAN:
Mommy!

1293
01:38:46,946 --> 01:38:48,780
Dylan!

1294
01:38:59,751 --> 01:39:02,336
Mommy!

1295
01:39:04,255 --> 01:39:05,589
[SCREAMS]

1296
01:39:13,973 --> 01:39:15,474
Come to Papa!

1297
01:39:16,851 --> 01:39:19,186
[DYLAN SCREAMING]

1298
01:39:20,355 --> 01:39:22,022
Gonna eat you up.

1299
01:39:25,568 --> 01:39:27,110
[SCREAMING]

1300
01:39:39,749 --> 01:39:41,625
No!

1301
01:39:45,505 --> 01:39:46,588
[SCREAMS]

1302
01:39:54,097 --> 01:39:56,431
[SNAKE HISSING]

1303
01:40:04,399 --> 01:40:06,066
Dylan! Get out of there!

1304
01:40:06,901 --> 01:40:08,193
-Hey!
-Aah!

1305
01:40:12,699 --> 01:40:14,825
[SCREAMING]

1306
01:40:23,334 --> 01:40:24,876
[SNAKES HISSING]

1307
01:40:36,681 --> 01:40:37,764
FREDDY:
No!

1308
01:40:47,025 --> 01:40:48,400
[GROANING]

1309
01:40:54,240 --> 01:40:55,490
HEATHER:
Push him in!

1310
01:41:04,375 --> 01:41:05,667
Push!

1311
01:41:23,728 --> 01:41:25,395
[SHRIEKING]

1312
01:41:32,403 --> 01:41:33,570
Run!

1313
01:42:06,938 --> 01:42:08,855
Are you okay?

1314
01:42:13,111 --> 01:42:16,446
Oh, my-- Honey. Honey.

1315
01:42:18,783 --> 01:42:20,784
Oh, my God.

1316
01:42:20,952 --> 01:42:24,037
We're saved. The witch is dead.

1317
01:42:24,205 --> 01:42:27,916
And his mother covered him with kisses,
and they were safe.

1318
01:42:39,595 --> 01:42:43,974
WES: Heather, thanks for having the guts
to play Nancy one last time.

1319
01:42:44,142 --> 01:42:46,643
At last Freddy's back where he belongs.

1320
01:42:46,811 --> 01:42:48,854
Regards, Wes.

1321
01:43:04,662 --> 01:43:07,164
Is it a story?

1322
01:43:07,331 --> 01:43:09,833
Yeah. It's a story.

1323
01:43:10,334 --> 01:43:12,419
DYLAN:
Read me some.

1324
01:43:14,714 --> 01:43:17,632
"We open on an old wooden bench.

1325
01:43:18,509 --> 01:43:22,596
There's fire and tools
and a man's grimy hands...

1326
01:43:22,764 --> 01:43:27,434
...building what soon is revealed
as a gleaming set of claws.

1327
01:43:27,602 --> 01:43:29,978
And the claws are moving now...

1328
01:43:30,146 --> 01:43:35,025
...as if awakening
from a long and unwanted sleep.

1329
01:43:35,193 --> 01:43:39,196
Then the man lays one trembling hand
flat upon the table...

1330
01:43:39,363 --> 01:43:43,408
...and with his other,
picks up a thick, sharp blade.

1331
01:43:43,576 --> 01:43:48,163
Behind the lights,
faces watch from the darkness...

1332
01:43:48,331 --> 01:43:53,168
...ready to laugh or scream in terror."



